{
{{- /* amazon-bedrock auth gating, per @canva/opencode-plugin-llmproxy README:

       VPN (no CODER env):
         The plugin fetches a bearer token via `otter` and injects it as the
         placeholder API key. The "llmproxy" placeholder MUST be present in
         auth.json — opencode only invokes the plugin's auth.loader for
         providers that have an entry, so without it the plugin never gets
         to do its bearer-token swap.

       Coder devbox (CODER=true):
         The plugin uses AWS IMDS credentials with SigV4 signing instead of
         a bearer token. Having a placeholder key here breaks that path —
         opencode picks up the placeholder and bypasses SigV4. So we omit
         the entry entirely on Coder.

       google + openai are unconditional: they route through the proxy in
       both modes (mTLS on Coder, VPN endpoint elsewhere), and both modes
       need the placeholder to wire up auth.loader. */ -}}
{{- if eq "" (env "CODER") }}
  "amazon-bedrock": { "type": "api", "key": "llmproxy" },
{{- end }}
  "google": { "type": "api", "key": "llmproxy" },
  "openai": { "type": "api", "key": "llmproxy" }
}
